ZH: 麻烦你帮我一个忙。
EN: Could you do me a favor?

ZH: 这种布料很麻。
EN: This fabric is very coarse.

ZH: 他的腿被蚊子咬得麻了。
EN: His leg was numb from mosquito bites.

ZH: 这道菜吃起来带点麻。
EN: This dish has a slightly numbing taste.

ZH: 我被荆棘刺到了，脚感觉麻麻的。
EN: I was pricked by thorns, and my foot feels numb.

ZH: 我今天早上起床时身体感觉很麻。
EN: I felt numb when I got up this morning.

ZH: 这个地方被冷风吹得麻了。
EN: This place was numbed by the cold wind.

ZH: 他紧张得手脚都麻了。
EN: He was so nervous that he felt numb all over.

ZH: 这个墙纸的质量很麻。
EN: The quality of this wallpaper is coarse.

ZH: 这种纱线摸起来很麻。
EN: This type of yarn feels rough to the touch.

ZH: 他的手指因为太长时间使用而麻木了。
EN: His fingers became numb from excessive use.

ZH: 这个面料手感很麻。
EN: The fabric has a rough texture.

ZH: 麻辣火锅是一种麻辣的菜肴。
EN: Spicy hot pot is a type of dish with numbing and spicy flavors.

ZH: 这个地方四周都是麻木的植物。
EN: Numb plants surrounded this area.

ZH: 他的腿酸痛而且麻。
EN: His legs were sore and numb.

ZH: 这种辣椒吃起来麻麻的。
EN: These peppers have a numbing sensation when eaten.

ZH: 蜜蜂的蜇会让皮肤麻麻的。
EN: A bee sting can make your skin feel numb.

ZH: 麻什么都不干，是不行的。
EN: Doing nothing and being numb is not a solution.

ZH: 爱因斯坦曾说过：“人生最重要的是不断摸索，这使人免于麻木。”
EN: Einstein once said: "The most important thing in life is to keep exploring, which prevents numbness."
